## âœ… **5. Understand `pom.xml`**

### ğŸ“„ Sample `pom.xml` Structure

```xml
<project>
  <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>

  <groupId>com.example</groupId>
  <artifactId>demo-project</artifactId>
  <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>

  <dependencies>
    <!-- Add dependencies here -->
  </dependencies>
</project>
```

---

## âœ… **6. Add Dependencies**

ğŸ“¦ Example: Add Gson for JSON parsing

Inside `<dependencies>` block in `pom.xml`:

```xml
<dependency>
  <groupId>com.google.code.gson</groupId>
  <artifactId>gson</artifactId>
  <version>2.10.1</version>
</dependency>
```

â¡ï¸ You can similarly add any other libraries.

---

## âœ… **7. Build Maven Project**

```bash
cd demo-project
mvn compile       # Compiles the code
mvn test          # Runs test cases
mvn package       # Creates JAR file in 'target' folder
```

---

## âœ… **8. Run the JAR File**

If you have a `main()` method in `App.java`, run:

```bash
java -cp target/demo-project-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar com.example.App
```

